What you need to know:

The relationship between the DP and his boss has lately been strained, with foreign diplomats pressuring President Kenyatta and the DP to tone down their political rhetoric.  Interior Principal Secretary Karanja Kibicho on Monday said between 3,000 and 3,500 people will sit inside the stadium while 8,500 more will watch the event from giant screens that will be strategically placed around Kisii town.